      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2023-05-11</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2023-07-20T13:35:13Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>First Responder Access to Innovative Technologies Act</strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to implement a uniform process for reviewing applications for certain anti-terrorism grants to urban areas and state, local, and tribal governments. </p> <p>Specifically, the uniform review must be done for grant applications requesting to purchase first responder equipment or systems that do not meet or exceed any applicable national voluntary consensus standards.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
